  <summary date="2020-05-20T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in Senate">National Guard COVID-19 Response Stability Act

This bill extends the authority of a&#160;governor of a state to maintain the National Guard on active duty in connection with the COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) public health emergency through the date that is 30 days after the termination of the emergency.</summary>
